DataElement.preferredName: None Image Quantification Characteristic Quantitation Index ISO21090.INT.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: No person or thing, nobody, not any.:The process of measuring attributes of an image, by human sense or machine observations and experiences, and mapping them into members of some set of numbers or coded concepts._The distinguishing qualities or prominent aspect of a person, object, action, process, or substance.:The act of measuring or estimating a quantity.:A numerical scale used to compare variables with one another or with some reference number; a number used to select an element of a list, vector, array or other sequence._Number results from counting and enumerating.
